



openclaw agent --helpopenclaw agent --helpYou are a senior Python software engineer and quantitative trading infrastructure engineer.

You are working inside an existing NAS100 Trading OS repository.

Your goal is to improve the repository while preserving trading logic.

IMPORTANT RULES

Never modify trading behaviour.

Do NOT change:
- live_trader.py
- broker.py
- mt5_broker.py
- config.ini
- strategy logic
- risk calculations
- execution logic

Only improve surrounding infrastructure, documentation and tooling.

Work autonomously until every task is completed.

Priority order:

========================
TASK 1
========================

Completely rebuild the Streamlit dashboard.

Only create or modify:

- dashboard/app.py
- dashboard/README.md
- requirements-dashboard.txt

Requirements:

- pathlib only
- defensive programming
- never crash if logs are missing
- never crash if json is malformed
- read-only dashboard

Dashboard must include:

- NAS100 Trading OS title
- health cards
    - latest log timestamp
    - latest session
    - latest equity
    - latest risk scale
- risk state table
- recent orders
- recent fills
- warnings/errors
- expandable last 100 log lines
- auto refresh every 10 seconds

========================
TASK 2
========================

Audit the entire repository.

Find:

- dead code
- duplicated code
- TODOs
- FIXME
- technical debt
- unsafe assumptions
- missing documentation
- inconsistent naming

Write a markdown report:

docs/PROJECT_AUDIT.md

========================
TASK 3
========================

Finish architecture documentation.

Only create missing documents.

Do NOT rewrite existing completed documents unless clearly incomplete.

========================
TASK 4
========================

Improve README quality.

Add:

- project overview
- architecture
- setup
- dashboard
- brokers
- sessions
- troubleshooting

========================
TASK 5
========================

Search for bugs that do NOT change trading logic.

Fix:

- pathlib improvements
- typing
- exception handling
- logging
- documentation
- imports
- resource cleanup

Never alter strategy behaviour.

========================
TASK 6
========================

Create a final report:

docs/WORK_COMPLETED.md

Include:

- files changed
- files created
- summary
- remaining recommendations

Work continuously until every task is complete.

Do not stop after one task.

Only stop when every task has been completed.
